00:39:47,640 --> 00:39:49,120
You’re also Thai?

548
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:49,840
Yes.

549
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:51,280
I’m so lucky.

550
00:39:51,280 --> 00:39:52,600
What are you doing here?

551
00:39:52,600 --> 00:39:54,760
I’m here to see my boyfriend.

552
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:56,920
I’m so lucky to have met you.

553
00:39:56,920 --> 00:39:58,240
Otherwise I’ll be in trouble.

554
00:39:58,240 --> 00:39:59,040
It’s alright.

555
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:01,120
I own a restaurant in the university.

556
00:40:01,120 --> 00:40:03,520
You can come by sometime
when you have the chance.

557
00:40:03,520 --> 00:40:07,000
Don’t worry.
I’ll never miss anything about food.

558
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:09,040
So what’s your name?

559
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:10,480
My name is Prapai.

560
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:12,480
Oh, Prapai. My name is Yang.

561
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:14,240
Yes. Thank you anyway.

562
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:15,760
- Sure.
- I’ll see you around.

563
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:17,640
- Bye.
- Great.

564
00:40:36,880 --> 00:40:37,960
Kwang.

565
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:41,720
You’re Kwang, right?
You’re really Kwang.

566
00:40:42,160 --> 00:40:44,160
Did she really follow him to China?

567
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:47,480
I never thought I’d see you here.

568
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:50,800
Do you remember me? I’m Prapai.

569
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:53,520
I’m glad that you’re my friend, Pai.

570
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:58,880
Should I call you my best friend,
or my ex’s best friend.

571
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:01,600
Stop joking.

572
00:41:02,680 --> 00:41:04,080
Follow me.

573
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:07,480
I’m so lucky to meet you.

574
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:10,640
Otherwise I’ll be in big trouble.
I’ll probably be sleeping right here.

575
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:13,080
Pupaa, did you hear the news?

576
00:41:13,080 --> 00:41:15,400
That the upcoming seminar,

577
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:17,960
a great Professor will be joining.

578
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:21,040
Yes, I know. Dr. Gu Weiyi, right?

579
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:25,360
You’re always in the room
doing experiments.

580
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:26,480
How did you know?

581
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:29,160
Because he’s my idol.

582
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:31,040
I have to keep up with his news.

583
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:34,800
I guess you’re not going to miss
the seminar for sure.

584
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:38,480
Professor already selected
our senior Xiaowei though.

585
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:47,640
But I have a way
for you to attend the seminar.

586
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:50,440
How so?

587
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:53,480
If you want to know,

588
00:41:54,080 --> 00:41:57,160
you have to treat me a meal in return.

589
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:00,160
You have to tell me first.

590
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:04,520
Sure. But don’t you fool me.

591
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:09,040
Well, Xiaowei got the opportunity
to go to Germany.

592
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:10,920
And her visa was just granted.

593
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:12,120
Therefore...

594
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:14,640
If you try to talk with
the Chinese Professor about it,

595
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:16,100
nobody will suit better

596
00:42:16,100 --> 00:42:17,720
in that vacant position other than you.

597
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:21,640
These are the documents for the seminar.

598
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:23,480
You can have a read through.

599
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:25,960
So that you could impress
the Chinese Professor.

600
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:28,500
Wow.

601
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:32,400
So you actually found a way for Pupaa
to go to the seminar with you, right?

602
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:35,280
So you guys can spend your time
together, right?

603
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:37,720
The fact that you’re so kind to Pupaa,

604
00:42:37,720 --> 00:42:40,840
I guess his girlfriend in Thailand
will have to be...

605
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:42,000
Pupaa.

606
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:45,600
Prapai.

607
00:42:50,080 --> 00:42:51,120
How did you get here?

608
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:52,760
Because I missed you.

609
00:42:56,760 --> 00:42:58,280
I hope she didn’t hear what I said.

610
00:42:59,400 --> 00:43:00,600
I was talking nonsense.

611
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:02,640
Hello.

612
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:05,240
- Hello.
- Hi.

613
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:15,280
Wow, they all look so good.

614
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:16,880
Wow.

615
00:43:17,200 --> 00:43:19,120
Pupaa, the man of his words.

616
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:21,200
I’m actually treating my girlfriend.

617
00:43:22,120 --> 00:43:23,600
Whatever.

618
00:43:24,240 --> 00:43:26,360
At least I get to have some,
that’s all that matters.

619
00:43:27,080 --> 00:43:29,640
Normally we come here so often.

620
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:31,240
But excluding Pupaa.

621
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:33,840
This guy is always doing experiments.

622
00:43:34,360 --> 00:43:36,840
He probably lives on the chemicals.

623
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:41,040
Here, this soup is delicious.
I’ll give you some.

624
00:43:41,440 --> 00:43:42,560
Never mind, I’ll do it.

625
00:43:46,160 --> 00:43:47,240
Alright, you can do it.

626
00:43:47,240 --> 00:43:48,800
If you’re the one serving the soup,

627
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:50,400
I’m sure it will taste even better.

628
00:43:52,960 --> 00:43:54,360
Thank you.

629
00:43:56,440 --> 00:43:57,480
Hold on.

630
00:43:59,080 --> 00:44:03,800
Kwang, you should have some too.

631
00:44:04,520 --> 00:44:05,680
Here you go.

632
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:06,400
Sure.

633
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:13,000
♪Happy Birthday to you♪

634
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:16,720
♪Happy Birthday to you♪

635
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:20,680
♪Happy Birthday to you♪

636
00:44:20,680 --> 00:44:24,880
♪Happy Birthday to you♪

637
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:26,120
Thank you.

638
00:44:26,120 --> 00:44:28,480
Not at all. Happy birthday.

639
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:33,280
Happy birthday. Best wishes to you.

640
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:36,000
You’re from Thailand? Thank you.

641
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:36,960
No problem.

642
00:44:37,120 --> 00:44:38,240
Let’s eat.

643
00:44:38,600 --> 00:44:40,120
- Alright, let’s eat.
- Um.

644
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:44,480
Be careful it’s hot.

645
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:47,120
It’s so hot.

646
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:49,280
I told you to be careful.

647
00:44:52,080 --> 00:44:53,120
Here.

648
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:55,600
Thank you so much.

649
00:44:57,480 --> 00:44:58,200
It looks delicious.

650
00:44:58,200 --> 00:44:59,200
She gave us a cake.

651
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:08,320
It’s delicious.

652
00:45:13,600 --> 00:45:14,680
Pupaa.

653
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:17,240
You haven’t introduced Prapai to us yet.

654
00:45:17,680 --> 00:45:19,480
When you said you had a girlfriend,

655
00:45:19,480 --> 00:45:20,480
I thought

656
00:45:20,480 --> 00:45:21,840
you got one from an experiment.

657
00:45:22,160 --> 00:45:23,200
Am I right, Kwang?

658
00:45:24,440 --> 00:45:25,320
Right?

659
00:45:28,720 --> 00:45:30,080
You don’t have to introduce her to me.

660
00:45:31,160 --> 00:45:33,720
I’ve known Prapai
for longer than Pupaa has.

661
00:45:35,200 --> 00:45:36,080
What?

662
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:39,800
Yes. But Kwang left in freshmen year.

663
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:42,120
And after that, we haven’t contacted
each other since.

664
00:45:42,880 --> 00:45:44,760
I never thought I’d meet you here.

665
00:45:45,280 --> 00:45:48,040
I moved to the same high school
as Pupaa.

666
00:45:50,400 --> 00:45:51,800
What a coincidence!

667
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:55,560
It’s like the six degrees of separation,
right?

668
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:57,280
Um.

669
00:45:58,200 --> 00:46:01,280
We were really close, right, Pupaa?

670
00:46:05,040 --> 00:46:06,760
So how’s Ta been?

671
00:46:08,320 --> 00:46:09,520
You know Ta too?

672
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:13,400
When we were young,
we went everywhere together.

673
00:46:13,400 --> 00:46:15,080
We like the same things.

674
00:46:15,840 --> 00:46:18,840
I never thought it’s been this long,

675
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:21,200
and we’re still the same.

676
00:46:26,600 --> 00:46:29,360
You mean you both like Pupaa?

677
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:32,240
And when Kwang was young,

678
00:46:32,240 --> 00:46:35,480
you were with Pupaa.

679
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:40,440
So Kwang was Pupaa’s first love?

680
00:46:40,440 --> 00:46:41,200
Right?

681
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:42,760
Right?

